BEHIND ALL THIS LAUGHTER

I laugh in the halls.
I smile up on stage.
I hug all of my friends.
I act a young age.
I laugh when I am tickled.
I talk in every class.
I look ever-so-happy,
Even if picked last.
But behind all of this,
All the hair, clothes, and eyes,
Is a person in despair,
A person in disguise.
I cry when I am hurt,
When I get cut I bleed.
I'm not always Miss Happy.
To my anger, I do cede.
My laughter is a cover,
My smiles are never real.
It's not like you ever care,
So I'll continue to conceal.

I hate what i say sometimes.

All i know is that i seem to not be like other girls.

It seems like all other girls catch onto things that i dont see.
It seems like every other girl wears make-up.

I dont know what happened to me.
Maybe something happened when i was young, to make me immune to girlish things,
Like what i said above.
It just feels like i'll never be like other girls.
Like i'll always be one step behind.
That i'll never notice things that others notice.
Sometimes i question why i'm like this.
Was it because i grew up with brother, thinking girls and boys acted the same?
I have no idea.
I just wished, sometimes, that I was more girlish. 
Or caught onto things that other girls do.
((sigh))
I guess I'll never know...

Ok. 
Now the poems.
My first one, which should be relatively happier than the second one:

THEY CAN SAY WHAT THEY WANT

People may call me stupid
Maybe even dumb
Maybe even crazy
Or maybe just a bum.
Maybe they call me ignorant
Or an insensitive creep
Some may call me ugly
While others call me cheap.
Maybe they say I'm a loser
While others call me mean
Maybe they don't care
Maybe they want to scream.
They might whisper behind my back
And say i shouldnt have said yes
But there's something i must say
Something that i must confess.
I've liked you since i met you
It wasn't long ago
I wanted to ask you out
But i was afraid you would say no.
But after you asked me out
There was no way I'd say no
I was so excited
But didn't let it show.
People can say I'm heartless
But i know that isn't true
The reason that i know this
Is because I love you.


That was my first poem.
A bit happy.
Idk.
Ok.
Now my second poem.
I dont have a name for it.
So it can be called: Nameless.

NAMELESS

My heart is beating fast
My nose is getting runny
My eyes are starting to water
Nothing seems sunny.
It feels like a cloud
Is following me overhead
Watching my every move
Wanting me to be dead.
I look straight in a mirror
And what do i see?
Tears streaming down my face
Full of sorrow and no glee.
Life seems to be a nightmare sometimes
Everyone hates me
Don't even try to lie
Just say that you agree.
What if i just left?
Would you even care?
Would you go out looking
In the nighttime air?
I can't pretend you care
Because I know you probably don't
Just, please don't say you'll be there for me,
If you really won't.


I'm not going through depression,
I just kind of sad and frusterated right now.
I'm ok.
Really.
I'm not really going to run away,
Or hurt myself,
Or anything.
I'm just blahish.
